---
description: Design-token and component-system rules for Uni Lions
alwaysApply: false
globs:
  - "src/**/*.{css,scss,ts,tsx}"
---

Read `knowledge/brand/visual-language.md`.

design-system:
- Define semantic tokens for color, typography, spacing, radius, shadow, container, and motion.
- Do not scatter raw brand hex values across components.
- Use a restrained radius system; avoid making every surface a floating card.
- Alternate light and dark sections intentionally.
- Keep body line length near 60–75 characters where practical.
- Maintain consistent section rhythm and container alignment.
- Primary CTA must have one canonical visual treatment.
- Secondary CTA must remain clearly secondary.
- Use border, tone, whitespace, and typography before adding shadows.
- Animation must clarify hierarchy or state, never decorate without purpose.
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`.
